title: Liouville's formula
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The solutions of the linear ODE $$\dot{Y}=A(t)Y,$$ where $$A,Y\colon \R \to \R^{n \times n}$$ satisfy
$$
\det Y(t) =
\det Y(t_0) \exp\left(
  \textstyle\int_{t_0}^t \tr A(s) \,\d s
\right).
$$